title: For Sale:  Ruger Super Blackhawk Predator by Mag-Na- Port/Shooting Industry Masters First Shots
postcontent: More than 350 industry representatives, ranging from top administrators and factory personnel to professional shooters, will compete in the 2013 Shooting Industry Masters shooting competition July 19-20 at the Cody Shooting Complex near Cody, Wyoming. A major component of the shoot will be fundraising events to benefit the National Shooting Sports Foundation (NSSF) First Shots program, which introduces thousands of new shooters to the shooting sports each year. Mag-Na-Port has been building and customizing firearms for decades, and is known for their remarkable work. Their craftsmanship is obvious in the visually stunning look of their products, and in the enhanced performance they deliver from their customized guns. For this very special project, Ruger donated a new Super Blackhawk single action revolver in the proven .44 Magnum caliber. Ken Kelly, guru of Mag-Na-Port, then customized this rugged handgun. The result is a field-friendly, powerful and handsome revolver! The final result is sure to please any handgun hunter or collector. Part of this stunning Ruger Predator package is this amazing cross-body leather rig by Karla VanHorn of Purdy Gear Leather. Karla's work has been featured in American Handgunner Magazine, and for obvious reasons. Hand tooled, this is literally "the best" in leather and is a great compliment to the Ruger Mag-Na-Port Predator .44 Magnum! Among the custom features are: Inverted muzzle crown Velvet hone finish Etch Mag-Na-Port Predator logo C-More front sight Omega outline rear sight blade Jewel and polish trigger and hammer Polished stripes on cylinder Polish center pin, C.P. release, ejector rod, pins and screws Mirror polish and jewel top strap Action job, check headspace, cylinder gap, alignment Set trigger pull to 3 pounds Re-cut forcing cone and number chambers *Note: Includes build sheet from Mag-Na-Port and Mag-Na-Port product catalog. This Ruger Superblackhawk Mag-Na-Port “Predator” model in .44 Magnum has been customized by Mag-Na-Port specifically for this special auction benefiting the NSSF First Shots program, and is an opportunity to both own an uncompromising hunting revolver — and to help keep our shooting sports growing! GunBroker.com clients can participate in the excitement of the Masters, and substantially support the NSSF’s First Shot’s Program by bidding on this very unusual and unique custom big-bore revolver! We welcome your participation in the auction for this Mag-Na-Port collectible, and appreciate your support of the important NSSF “First Shots” program!

The engine started life as a 1600cc type 1.with an aftermarket aluminum case. it has a 84mm stroker FORGED SCAT Volksracer Crankshaft, Forged Piston and Cylinder Kit, 4340 SCAT Chromoly Gland Nut and HD Washer, 4340 H beam Forged Rods,SCAT Cam, SCAT Lightweight Lifters, HD Chromoly Pushrods, Gasket Set and Silicone Flywheel Seal, HD Oil Pump, Main Bearings, Rod Bearings, and Cam Bearings.Aluminum performance Crankshaft Pulley. it is a dual port with custom made intake ramd that go to a holley 500 blow threw carb. all air tight

The trans is a trans from a 70 -75 vw bus. thay are the best to be used on sand rails and dune buggys. all of the pro shops use these. it is a bus type 2 irs syle 091. 4.57 Ring and Pinion Ratio, weddle Gear Sets 1st thru 4th, Super Diff, 6 rib 4 speed with rev. has prosche heavy duty axles. the rail has doetsch tech high performance shocks on the rear, i cant find out wut style are on the front 

It is a 2 seater with 2 race bucket seats with 4 point harnesses,thay have seen there fair share of weather and could use been replaced. in the drivers cock pit u have gas peddle, brake peddle with its own master cylinder,and clutch pedel. in between the driver seat and pas is a gemuine neal brake lever. it looks like a e brake but if u push it down it brakes the pas side raer tire and if u pull it up it brakes the driver rear. this set up is so when u are doin a wheelie u can turn the rail with the front tires in the air. on the roof above the driver seat u have a toggle ingnition set up.not the cheap one. u have toggles that run everything. has ones for the high flow fuel pump,headlights,taillights,lights on the gauges,and a light that is over the engine bay just in case u have to work on it at night. has oil temp gauge,bosst gauge and a few others.
The sand rail is titled as a 90s model gmc sanoma. im not 100% sure how thay did this but it works for the dmv and police,so it worked for me. only thing the rail needs to e 100% street legal is turn signals, and depending on the state it might need a windshield but a helmet works just as good.
When i got the sand rail the guys had made a custom built trailer to haul it on. it will go with the rail. it has both new wheel bearings and is ready to go. it is not a show trailer just something to haul it around on.
i am looking to trade it for a 4x4 truck of a big lifted 4 wheeler. i will look at all offers but i dnt want any 4cyl cars, or boats. unless it is 2 good jet skis. i am really looing for something like a k5 blazer lifted and road and mud ready. my toy runs and drives great ur trade offer has to also. i know wut i have i know how much it would cost to build one just like this so trade offers have to be at least 6k, or ur offer and guns or cash txt me ONLY if u call i will not pick up. title: For Sale/Trade:   M31 Suomi Finnish $500 with out extras $600 with with extras
postcontent:
Comes with 1- 36 round stick mag.For $600 you get 7 stick mags  and a 71 round drum . Cheap and fun to shoot. Look them up on you tube they are accurate at 500 + yards.Local Mo residents only face to face and I will not drive to far.The mags still have the grease from the factory on them that's why they look dirty. Must be 21 for me to sell it to you. Now about the rifle .

 World War II. It was a descendant of the M-22 prototype and the KP/-26 production model, which was revealed to the public in 1925. The Suomi-konepistooli KP/-31 is often abbreviated to Suomi KP.

The Suomi KP/-31 is regarded by many[3] as one of the most successful submachine guns of World War II, also the soon developed 71-round drum magazine was later copied and adopted by the Soviets for their PPD-40 and PPSh-41 submachine guns.[4] The accuracy of the Suomi was superior to that of the mass-produced PPSh-41,[4] thanks in part to a noticeably longer barrel, with the same rate of fire and the equally large magazine capacity.[4] The major disadvantage of the Suomi KP/-31 was its high production costs.

The Suomi KP/-31 also incorporated a few new design features, including an arrangement whereby the spring was mounted inside the bolt in order to make the gun shorter. Its 50-round quad-column "Casket" box magazine was more reliable than the early 40-round "bullets loaded nose down" drum magazine, and similar applications were used on the Argentinian C-4 submachine gun and present-day 60-round 5.45x39mm AK-74 compatible magazines.

The M-22 and KP/-26 were made by Konepistooli Oy, founded by Master Armorer Aimo Lahti, Captain V. Korpela, Lieutenant Y. Koskinen and Lieutenant L. Boyer-Spoof. The Suomi KP/-31 was designed by Koskinen and Lahti.

The Suomi KP/-31 went into serial production in 1931 by Tikkakoski Oy and most of these weapons were bought by the Finnish Defence Forces. The Finnish Defence Forces were equipped with about 4000 Suomi KP/-31 submachine guns when the Winter War started. During the course of the war, the design was altered with the addition of a muzzle brake, which increased the submachine gun's overall length by 55 mm. The revised version was designated KP/-31 SJR (suujarru, or "muzzle brake"). Aimo Lahti was displeased with this revision, believing that it decreased muzzle velocity and reduced the weapon's reliability, and even sought in vain to have the muzzle brake's designer court-martialed. Ultimately, roughly half of the KP/-31s in Finnish service were of the SJR version. Initially the KP/-31 was issued as a substitute for a light machine gun, and proved inadequate in this role. Instead, soldiers learned by trial and error how to use submachine guns to the best effect. By the time of the Continuation War, Finnish doctrine had been altered to include both a KP/-31 and a light machine gun (usually a captured Degtyaryov DP) in every infantry squad, and by 1943 this had been expanded to two KP/-31s per squad. KP/-31 production continued with the intention of adding a third sub machine gun to each squad, but this plan was shelved in 1944 when the Continuation War ended..

Reciprocity is when one state agrees to honor another states permit, meaning you can then carry in another state.

CCW applications will be available at class

Class runs from 08:00am-5:00pm

About the class-
Classroom and Range are at the same location.

We have guns in 22, 9mm, 38 special and 45 acp.

FOID not needed to take the class as long as you are not a prohibited person, if you could legally own a gun but are waiting for your FOID card then you can take the class.

Firearm Safety, this is first and foremost a firearm safety class, the only way to fail is to be dangerous on the range/classroom.
Types of handguns- Revolvers / Semiautomatics
Actions- Single Action only / Double Action-Single Action / Double Action Only / Striker Fired
Major parts of a Revolver, Frame, Barrel, Cylinder, trigger, trigger guard, handgrips, etc.
Major parts of a Semi Automatic- Frame, Barrel, magazine, trigger guard, handgrips, etc.
Ammunition- Centerfire / Rimfire, Full Jacketed / Lead, Hollow Point / Wadcutter / Round nose
How to pick the right ammo for your gun- Caliber, Standard pressure / +P pressure ,
Ex. Learn the difference between different 9mm rounds
9mm Luger, 9mm Parabellum, 9mm NATO, 9mmx19mm (all the same round, just different names.
9x18 or 9mm Makerov different ammo and I've seen people buy it for their 9mm Parabellum guns and it wouldn't work.
There are many more ammunition differences to watch out for, like 45 ACP vs 45 GAP vs 45 Colt.

Shooting stances- Isosceles, Weaver, Single handed and proper grip.
Fundamentals of shooting- Breath control, sight alignment, trigger control, follow through.

Cover laws on firearm purchasing and transport.
Learn about other shooting opportunities.

And much more.

Private classes, ladies only, weekday and weeknight classes available.
Please contact with your availability, we are trying to schedule more classes to meet students needs.

Contact us for more info or to inquire about additional class availability.
